The paper focuses on using a deep neural network physics model as a coarse model for Parareal in the context of robotic manipulation. This involves planning and control algorithms, which are typically associated with robotics (cs.RO). The use of a deep neural network also suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The experiments involve simulating and manipulating multiple objects, which suggests a focus on systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the experiments also involve visual perception and image processing, which suggests a focus on computer vision (cs.CV).
